(39, 'RFK Jr. must remain on the Michigan ballot, judge says', 14, 19, '<p style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: 1.55; font-size: 18px; font-stretch: normal; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">LANSING, Mich. (AP) â€” A Michigan judge ruled that&nbsp;<span class=\"LinkEnhancement\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px);\"><a class=\"Link AnClick-LinkEnhancement\" data-gtm-enhancement-style=\"LinkEnhancementA\" href=\"https://apnews.com/hub/robert-f-kennedy-jr\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px); touch-action: manipulation; color: var(--color-link-text); text-decoration-line: underline;\">Robert F. Kennedy Jr</a></span>. must remain on the November presidential ballot, dealing a blow to his crusade to strategically remove his ticket from the battleground state.</font></p><p style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: 1.55; font-size: 18px; font-stretch: normal; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Kennedy&nbsp;<span class=\"LinkEnhancement\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px);\"><a class=\"Link AnClick-LinkEnhancement\" data-gtm-enhancement-style=\"LinkEnhancementA\" href=\"https://apnews.com/article/rfk-jr-trump-speech-arizona-a2638f89ddcb5de03edbe4574ca17d45\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px); touch-action: manipulation; color: var(--color-link-text); text-decoration-line: underline;\">suspended his campaign and endorsed former President Donald Trump</a></span>&nbsp;in August. Since then, he has sought to withdraw his name in states â€” like Michigan â€” where the race could be close. At the same time, he is trying to&nbsp;<span class=\"LinkEnhancement\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px);\"><a class=\"Link AnClick-LinkEnhancement\" data-gtm-enhancement-style=\"LinkEnhancementA\" href=\"https://apnews.com/article/north-carolina-kennedy-ballot-elections-board-d59aeb239392e4c6800df89e01f666ed\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px); touch-action: manipulation; color: var(--color-link-text); text-decoration-line: underline;\">remain on the ballot in states</a></span>&nbsp;where he is unlikely to make a difference between Trump and Vice President Kamala Harris.</font></p><p style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: 1.55; font-size: 18px; font-stretch: normal; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Kennedy filed a lawsuit Friday in Michiganâ€™s Court of Claims against Secretary of State Jocelyn Benson, a Democrat, in an effort to withdraw his name. Michiganâ€™s election officials had previously rejected Kennedyâ€™s notice of withdrawal.</font></p><p style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: 1.55; font-size: 18px; font-stretch: normal; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">The Associated Press asked the secretaryâ€™s office for comment on the Court of Claims order that came down Tuesday.</font></p><p style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: 1.55; font-size: 18px; font-stretch: normal; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">In a&nbsp;<span class=\"LinkEnhancement\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px);\"><a class=\"Link AnClick-LinkEnhancement\" data-gtm-enhancement-style=\"LinkEnhancementA\" href=\"https://x.com/JocelynBenson/status/1830980667817013664\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px); touch-action: manipulation; color: var(--color-link-text); text-decoration-line: underline;\">post on X</a></span>&nbsp;earlier in the day, Benson said under Michigan law, candidates who are nominated and accept a minor partyâ€™s nomination â€œshall not be permitted to withdraw.â€</font></p><p style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: 1.55; font-size: 18px; font-stretch: normal; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Kennedy argued in the lawsuit that his notice of withdrawal was timely and the electorateâ€™s votes could be â€œdiminished and rendered invalidâ€ if he remains on the ballot. He filed a similar lawsuit in&nbsp;<span class=\"LinkEnhancement\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px);\"><a class=\"Link AnClick-LinkEnhancement\" data-gtm-enhancement-style=\"LinkEnhancementA\" href=\"https://apnews.com/article/rfk-north-carolina-ballot-774664e6fb82a14d5f62f46d87f90399\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px); touch-action: manipulation; color: var(--color-link-text); text-decoration-line: underline;\">North Carolina</a></span>&nbsp;on Friday, where he is trying to withdraw his name from the ballot.</font></p><p style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: 1.55; font-size: 18px; font-stretch: normal; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Michigan Court of Claims Judge Christopher P. Yates concluded that the secretary of state rightly rejected Kennedyâ€™s request to be removed from the ballot.</font></p><div class=\"HTMLModuleEnhancement\" data-align-center=\"\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px); --marginForExtraSpace: -20px; margin: var(--marginForExtraSpace) 0; align-items: center; display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; font-size: 18px;\"><div class=\"HTMLModuleEnhancement-item\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px); width: 720px; display: flex; justify-content: center;\"><div class=\"HTMLModuleEnhancement-embed\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px); --color-video-bg: #fff; min-width: calc(100% + 80px);\"><div class=\"HtmlModule\" data-module-tracksubscribe=\"\" data-gtm-topic=\"No Value\" data-module-number=\"2\" data-main-module-number=\"2\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px);\"><a class=\"AnchorLink\" id=\"html-embed-module-e30000\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px); touch-action: manipulation; color: var(--color-link-text); display: block; height: 0px; pointer-events: none; position: absolute; scroll-margin-top: calc(var(--headerHeight) + var(--hatHeight) + 20px); visibility: hidden;\"></a><div class=\"taboola_readmore\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px);\"></div><p class=\"embed-caption\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px); color: var(--color-primary-text); font-size: 13px; font-stretch: semi-condensed;\"></p></div></div></div></div><p style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: 1.55; font-size: 18px; font-stretch: normal; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">â€œElections are not just games, and the Secretary of State (SOS) is not obligated to honor the whims of candidates for public office,â€ Yates said in his opinion and order.</font></p><p style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: 1.55; font-size: 18px; font-stretch: normal; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Aaron Siri, an attorney for Kennedy in the Michigan lawsuit, said that keeping Kennedyâ€™s name â€œupends ballot integrity.â€</font></p><p style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: 1.55; font-size: 18px; font-stretch: normal; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">â€œWe agree with the judge that elections are not games, and that is precisely why the court should have let Robert F. Kennedy, Jr. withdraw from the ballot,â€ Siri said in a written statement.</font></p><p style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: 1.55; font-size: 18px; font-stretch: normal; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Speaking on Fox News Channelâ€™s â€œThe Story with Martha MacCallumâ€ on Tuesday, Kennedy said, â€œWeâ€™re trying to get off the ballot in all the states where I might be a spoiler and cause harm to President Trump.â€</font></p><p style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: 1.55; font-size: 18px; font-stretch: normal; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span class=\"LinkEnhancement\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px);\"><a class=\"Link AnClick-LinkEnhancement\" data-gtm-enhancement-style=\"LinkEnhancementA\" href=\"https://apnews.com/article/wisconsin-robert-kennedy-cornel-west-jill-stein-3cef5d4716e7650a1a113d7ebc45d6cc\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px); touch-action: manipulation; color: var(--color-link-text); text-decoration-line: underline;\">Wisconsin</a></span>&nbsp;election officials said last week that Kennedy must remain on the ballot there, rejecting his request to withdraw.</font></p><p style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: 1.55; font-size: 18px; font-stretch: normal; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Last week, a different Michigan Court of Claims judge ruled that liberal independent candidate for president&nbsp;<span class=\"LinkEnhancement\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px);\"><a class=\"Link AnClick-LinkEnhancement\" data-gtm-enhancement-style=\"LinkEnhancementA\" href=\"https://apnews.com/article/cornel-west-michigan-ballot-ruling-4eecb8eddec7db7d17f6d82686286354\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px); touch-action: manipulation; color: var(--color-link-text); text-decoration-line: underline;\">Cornel West</a></span>&nbsp;must remain on the ballot, an opinion welcomed by Westâ€™s campaign.</font></p><p style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: 1.55; font-size: 18px; font-stretch: normal; margin-top: 20px;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Kennedy and West, prominent third-party candidates, are at the center of multiple legal and political battles across the country as Democrats and Republicans seek to use the impacts of third-party candidates who could take support from their opponents. Republican allies in&nbsp;<span class=\"LinkEnhancement\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px);\"><a class=\"Link AnClick-LinkEnhancement\" data-gtm-enhancement-style=\"LinkEnhancementA\" href=\"https://apnews.com/article/cornel-west-jill-stein-republican-network-harris-4089fb0c9ebb16002e56a1c254a21b0e\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px); touch-action: manipulation; color: var(--color-link-text); text-decoration-line: underline;\">multiple battleground states</a></span>&nbsp;such as&nbsp;<span class=\"LinkEnhancement\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px);\"><a class=\"Link AnClick-LinkEnhancement\" data-gtm-enhancement-style=\"LinkEnhancementA\" href=\"https://apnews.com/article/ballot-deception-cornel-west-conservatives-0d2c94da68bbd136442e63edadf14398\" style=\"background-repeat: no-repeat; line-height: calc(1em + 4px); touch-action: manipulation; color: var(--color-link-text); text-decoration-line: underline;\">Arizona</a></span>&nbsp;and Michigan have sought to keep West on the ballot amid Democratic fears he could siphon votes from Vice President Kamala Harris.</font></p>', '2024-09-04 00:08:39', NULL, 1, 'RFK-Jr.-must-remain-on-the-Michigan-ballot,-judge-says', '6f5047150da5443ceb15fb3120db8195.png'),
(40, 'Deadpool and Wolverine isnâ€™t just a bad movie â€“ itâ€™s changing the definition of what a â€˜movieâ€™ is', 11, 16, '<p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">hat is a movie? It sounds like a silly question, perhaps, but itâ€™s one thatâ€™s been rattling around my head ever since I walked out of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/reviews/deadpool-wolverine-review-ryan-reynolds-hugh-jackman-b2586281.html\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\"><em>Deadpool &amp; Wolverine&nbsp;</em></a>last Friday. Marvelâ€™s cameo-stuffed, fourth-wall-breaking superhero sequel made a staggering $438.3m across its opening weekend â€“ a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/ryan-reynolds-deadpool-wolverine-box-office-records-b2587461.html\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">record for an R-rated film</a>. It feels in many ways like a watershed moment. But not a good one. If we are watching, as some critics have suggested, the death of cinema happen before our eyes, then itâ€™s taken the form of a public execution.</font></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">There have been plenty of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/deadpool-wolverine-reviews-critics-release-date-b2586295.html\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">â€œworseâ€ movies than&nbsp;<em>Deadpool &amp; Wolverine</em></a>. Even within the remit of Marvelâ€™s own conveyor-belt oeuvre, last yearâ€™s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/ant-man-and-the-wasp-quantumania-review-jonathan-majors-b2294699.html\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\"><em>Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania</em></a>&nbsp;and 2022â€™s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/chris-hemsworth-thor-love-and-thunder-b2537429.html\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\"><em>Thor: Love and Thunder</em></a>&nbsp;were far messier affairs â€“ structurally chaotic and aesthetically rebarbative to an extent that&nbsp;<em>Deadpool &amp; Wolverine&nbsp;</em>is not. But&nbsp;<em>Deadpool&nbsp;</em>feels somehow the most cynical of all of the canon to date, the most spiritually and creatively bereft. It is a film that is about absolutely nothing â€“ a film with no discernable purpose or artistic ambitions, beyond the perpetuation of its own corporate myth.</font></p><div id=\"article-im-prompt\" style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: medium;\"></div><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">There are jokes about the Disney-Fox merger. Jokes about producer Kevin Feige. Jokes about the widespread disillusionment towards the Marvel franchise. Around halfway through the film, the two eponymous leads&nbsp;(played by Ryan Reynolds and Hugh Jackman, the latter exhuming â€“ literally at one point â€“ his famous X-Men character) encounter a team of throwback superheroes: Jennifer Garnerâ€™s Elektra, Wesley Snipesâ€™ Blade, Chris Evansâ€™s Johnny Storm (from&nbsp;<em>Fantastic Four</em>), Channing Tatumâ€™s Gambit (never produced) and Dafne Keenâ€™s mini-Wolverine from&nbsp;<em>Logan</em>.</font></p><div class=\"sc-w27hnf-3 glAnFg desktop-only teads\" style=\"margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: medium;\"><div class=\"sc-1y9ieyw-0 fZKFoR\" style=\"position: relative; max-width: 100%; justify-content: center; margin: 0px auto; background-color: transparent; clear: both;\"><div class=\"sc-1pfx6hk-0 kBYRNf\" style=\"max-width: 100%;\"><div data-mpu=\"true\" data-is-video=\"false\" data-tile-name=\"thirdparty01\" data-ad-unit-path=\"/71347885/_partner_independent/in_arts-entertainment/in_films/image/thirdparty01\" data-size-key=\"THIRD_PARTY_ARTICLE_BODY_DESKTOP\" data-refresh-check=\"false\" data-refresh-ms=\"150000\"></div></div></div></div><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">The film invites us to gawp at these comebacks. Meta-referential dialogue explains that these characters, ostensibly stuck in some kind of out-of-universe â€œvoidâ€, are simply trying to&nbsp;<em>get the endings they deserve</em>. What these â€œdeserved endingsâ€ actually look like in practice is fewer than 10 lines of dialogue apiece â€“ in Snipesâ€™ case, mostly just repeating catchphrases from the first three&nbsp;<em>Blade&nbsp;</em>films â€“ before they all drive out to a skirmish in the desert and get swallowed up by some kind of deadly CGI air monster. Thereâ€™s no attempt at characterisation, no point behind the meta-joke. The insistence that audiences are for some reason gagging to see Reynoldsâ€™ Deadpool exchange one line of insipid banter with Tatumâ€™s Gambit, is baffling. Audiences didnâ€™t love&nbsp;<em>Blade&nbsp;</em>because Snipes just showed up, stood there and barked catchphrases â€“ he was part of a story, with a proper character, and stakes, and intentionality. That Marvel cannot see the difference â€“ or, even worse, if it can see the difference but chooses to ignore it â€“ is surely damning.</font></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Itâ€™s telling, too, that Reynolds has spent much of the&nbsp;<em>Deadpool &amp; Wolverine&nbsp;</em>press tour performatively retching in the vague direction of&nbsp;<em>Green Lantern</em>, his critically panned 2011 DC Comics blockbuster that, were it owned by Marvel and not DC, would surely have been reclaimed here as a â€œforgotten gemâ€ along with the other dross.</font></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">To be clear,&nbsp;<em>Deadpool &amp; Wolverine&nbsp;</em>is not the first movie of its kind. In many ways, itâ€™s simply re-applying the lessons learned from 2021â€™s&nbsp;<em>Spider-Man: No Way Home&nbsp;</em>â€“ a film that made waves (and nearly $2bn) with a glut of surprise cameos, giving Tobey Maguire, Andrew Garfield and more the chance to reprise their bygone Spider-Man roles. But even that film offered more in the way of story and purpose than&nbsp;<em>Deadpool &amp; Wolverine</em>. Garfield, Maguire and co were given the barest bones of character arcs, to play around with as they saw fit. (Garfield ended up making considerably more of the opportunity.)</font></p><div class=\"sc-toncsa-0 jQFbah\" style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: medium;\"></div><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">If youâ€™ll allow me to get a little philosophical about things: how do we define what is and isnâ€™t a movie? Over the past two decades, Marvel has re-shaped Hollywood in its own image, whittling away some of the things that made filmmaking unique as an art form and shifting it towards something more televisual and serialised. We call&nbsp;<em>Deadpool &amp; Wolverine&nbsp;</em>a movie because it is released in cinemas, and is two hours long, but other than these technicalities, it shares almost nothing with a traditional blockbuster, when it comes to intent. The problem isnâ€™t that it tells its story badly â€“ itâ€™s that it has no interest in telling a story well at all. Itâ€™s interested exclusively in the maintenance and consolidation of Marvelâ€™s brand, in its viability as both product and advertisement, a snake eating its own tail.</font></p><div class=\"sc-chxdj2-0 IqJXP\" style=\"max-width: 100%; clear: both; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: medium;\"><figure class=\"sc-1cbdeug-0 bGOAvs\" style=\"position: relative;\"><div class=\"sc-1mu3l86-0 fESIQl\" style=\"max-width: 100%;\"><div id=\"video_holder\" class=\"sc-1mu3l86-3 eLPuxS\"><div class=\"sc-1mu3l86-1 cXFFUm\" style=\"position: relative;\"><div class=\"sc-knesRu buabvA\" style=\"position: relative; overflow: hidden; padding-bottom: 351px;\"><iframe src=\"https://cdn.jwplayer.com/players/99Wcz592-9ygSIn9G.html\" width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"auto\" style=\"position: absolute;\"></iframe></div></div></div></div><figcaption class=\"sc-1cbdeug-1 sc-1cbdeug-3 ixoBTH ddQYMd\" style=\"color: rgb(100, 100, 100); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; padding: 8px 16px; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 247);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Deadpool &amp; Wolverine trailer</font></figcaption></figure></div><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">â€œTurn off your brain and enjoy it for what it is,â€ has become the prevailing mantra of the&nbsp;<em style=\"\">Deadpool&nbsp;</em>defenders on social media. And of course, people are allowed to enjoy what they like. But freebasing cocaine is surely enjoyable to many people; that doesnâ€™t mean we should all get on board with its production and distribution.&nbsp;If cinema starts losing the notion that it even ought to function as a work of art â€“ if it becomes not just&nbsp;<em style=\"\">bad art</em>, but some new and insidious other thing â€“ then the jig, as it were, is truly up. If&nbsp;<em style=\"\">Deadpool &amp; Wolverine&nbsp;</em>is what the future of cinema looks like, itâ€™ll take more than a few plucky heroes to save it.</font></p>', '2024-09-04 00:30:10', NULL, 1, 'Deadpool-and-Wolverine-isnâ€™t-just-a-bad-movie-â€“-itâ€™s-changing-the-definition-of-what-a-â€˜movieâ€™-is', '6e67c1809957b82c69de7f6b90bf6acd.jpg'),
(41, 'The Rings of Power season two review: Like a mirthless rollercoaster ride, rarely fraught with any tension', 11, 16, '<p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">â€œAll Middle-earth balances on the brink of the abyss,â€ whispers the Dark Lord Sauron, ominously. And so it proves, in this second season of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/amazon-prime\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">Prime Video</a>â€™s&nbsp;<em style=\"\">The Lord of the Rings:&nbsp;</em><a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/the-rings-of-power\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\"><em>The Rings of Power</em></a>. Fragile truces will break, new alliances will be brokered â€“ and in the fires of the great furnace, 16 more rings will be forged. This is&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/jrr-tolkien\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">JRR Tolkien</a>â€™s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/news/lord-of-the-rings-tom-bombadil-rory-kinnear-b2553807.html\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">fantastical vision&nbsp;</a>rendered on a big scale, for the small screen.</font></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">At Rivendell, the elves are in crisis. Last season, Galadriel (<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/morfydd-clark\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">Morfydd Clark</a>) is still reeling from the discovery that she was in cahoots â€“&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/news/lord-of-the-rings-of-power-galadriel-sauron-b2586783.html\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">and almost in love&nbsp;</a>â€“ with Sauron (Charlie Vickers), who had disguised himself as a harmless mortal. Now, Sauron is off to forge his own ring â€“ leaving Galadriel and estranged bestie Elrond (Robert Aramayo) to bicker about the use of the three sparkling elvish rings. Meanwhile, the strange wizard who may or may not be Gandalf (Daniel Weyman) is marching through the deadlands of RhÃ»n with his harfoot companions, PharazÃ´n (Trystan Gravelle) is once again angling for power in NÃºmenor, and Isildur (<em>Mr Beanâ€™s Holiday</em>â€™s Maxim Baldry) is forging his own path across Middle-earth. Thatâ€™s not to mention all the other characters â€“ with word-count destroyingly long names â€“ who are off on their own adventures.</font></p><div id=\"article-im-prompt\" style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: medium;\"></div><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">â€œSauron sees himself not as master of a barren waste,â€ comes Galadrielâ€™s judgement of her ex. â€œBut of all Middle-earth.â€ And so the tease that began in the first season of&nbsp;<em>Rings of Power</em>&nbsp;comes into full force: rings are made, armies are sought, power is gained. Unlike its release schedule sibling,&nbsp;<em>House of the Dragon</em>, there can be no accusations of delayed gratification. The greatest hits of the Tolkien saga â€“ from balrogs to palantirs â€“ get wheeled out. Clark â€“ the most convincing performer in this new interpretation of the mythology â€“ is only a side player this season, as the action jumps from Khazad-dÃ»m to Lindon, by way of the fires of Mordor. And adding to the sense of grandeur, several familiar faces from British stage and screen â€“ CiarÃ¡n Hinds, Rory Kinnear, Jack Lowden â€“ are added to the ensemble.</font></p><div class=\"sc-w27hnf-3 glAnFg desktop-only teads\" style=\"margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: medium;\"><div class=\"sc-1y9ieyw-0 fZKFoR\" style=\"position: relative; max-width: 100%; justify-content: center; margin: 0px auto; background-color: transparent; clear: both;\"><div class=\"sc-1pfx6hk-0 kBYRNf\" style=\"max-width: 100%;\"><div data-mpu=\"true\" data-is-video=\"false\" data-tile-name=\"thirdparty01\" data-ad-unit-path=\"/71347885/_partner_independent/in_arts-entertainment/in_tv/video/thirdparty01\" data-size-key=\"THIRD_PARTY_ARTICLE_BODY_DESKTOP\" data-refresh-check=\"false\" data-refresh-ms=\"150000\"></div></div></div></div><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">But even they struggle with the material. Delivering ominous dialogue about shadows descending across various kingdoms, or even just making old-timey small talk, requires a level of belief in the project. Merely reading the lines â€“ however competent the delivery â€“ results in something that feels like a high-octane table read. You must be willing to inhabit your character: â€œI&nbsp;<em>am</em>&nbsp;a displaced Middle-earther on the hunt for orcs.â€ And too often in&nbsp;<em>Rings of Power,</em>&nbsp;the desire to spend the lavish budget on sets and effects has resulted in casting decisions that undermine this principle. These are young, beautiful actors who look like they should be sipping coffee on a squishy sofa in a Dunelm catalogue, rather than smeared with mud and blood, traipsing across a lawless wilderness.</font></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">But&nbsp;<em>Rings of Power&nbsp;</em>has always struggled with creating an internal verisimilitude. When Arondir (Ismael Cruz CÃ³rdova) returns in this second outing, it is a stark reminder of the showâ€™s issues with its own reality. The fights are filled with needless spins and wiggles â€“ like theyâ€™ve been choreographed by Raygun â€“ allowing jeopardy to escape in the process. Similarly, so much expositional work is done in every conversation that they rarely feel fraught with&nbsp;<em>actual</em>&nbsp;tension. Moments where the show comes close to dealing with emotion (â€œIâ€™m as hard as you, as stubborn as you,â€ Durin (Owain Arthur) tells his father, â€œI was wrong to disrespect youâ€) are superseded by a desire to make broad points. â€œThe hearts of men are easily corrupted,â€ Galadriel tells us, but everyone else â€“ dwarves, elves, wizards â€“ seem locked in an intransigent archetype.</font></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">There has always been something slightly&nbsp;<em style=\"\">wrong</em>&nbsp;about&nbsp;<em style=\"\">The Rings of Power</em>. A visual aesthetic that seemed to take more from Peter Jacksonâ€™s derided&nbsp;Hobbit&nbsp;films than his acclaimed trilogy. A wigginess to the character design that makes it look more like&nbsp;<em style=\"\">Doctor Who</em>&nbsp;than prestige drama. A proliferation of MacGuffins â€“ objects that catalyse the plot â€“ that would shame even Michael Bay. A temptation towards fan service, shoehorning characters like Tom Bombadil into the already overstuffed action. An indulgent belief that â€œepicâ€ means every interaction must be portentous â€“ and that humour must be eschewed at all costs. The result is like being on a mirthless rollercoaster ride: thrown around, spun upside down, but always wondering when the fun is supposed to kick in.</font></p>', '2024-09-04 00:34:47', NULL, 1, 'The-Rings-of-Power-season-two-review:-Like-a-mirthless-rollercoaster-ride,-rarely-fraught-with-any-tension', '3fb2db6cccf4a23383383394b28b2b31.jpg'),
(42, 'Apollo 13: Eerie documentary shows what itâ€™s like to be stranded in space', 12, 17, '<p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">A new documentary chronicling the events surrounding the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/apollo\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">Apollo</a>&nbsp;13 mission, in which&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/tech/apollo-13-nasa-anniversary-moon-what-happened-explained-a9459771.html\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">three astronauts found themselves stranded in space</a>&nbsp;following a catastrophic explosion, is being released on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/netflix\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">Netflix</a>&nbsp;this week.</font></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\"><em>Apollo 13: Survival</em>&nbsp;uses archive material and rare access to the complete audio recordings of the mission of astronauts Jim Lovell, Jack Swigert and Fred Haise.</font></p><div id=\"article-im-prompt\" style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: medium;\"></div><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">The event was adapted into an Oscar-winning film&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/features/tom-hanks-movies-best-list-forrest-gump-saving-private-ryan-big-mister-rogers-a9304451.html\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">starring Tom Hanks in 1995</a>, but is documented in a historical format with never-before-seen footage, and interviews with the original team for the first time.</font></p><div class=\"sc-w27hnf-3 glAnFg desktop-only teads\" style=\"margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: medium;\"><div class=\"sc-1y9ieyw-0 fZKFoR\" style=\"position: relative; max-width: 100%; justify-content: center; margin: 0px auto; background-color: transparent; clear: both;\"><div class=\"sc-1pfx6hk-0 kBYRNf\" style=\"max-width: 100%;\"><div data-mpu=\"true\" data-is-video=\"false\" data-tile-name=\"thirdparty01\" data-ad-unit-path=\"/71347885/_partner_independent/in_arts-entertainment/in_tv/video/thirdparty01\" data-size-key=\"THIRD_PARTY_ARTICLE_BODY_DESKTOP\" data-refresh-check=\"false\" data-refresh-ms=\"150000\"></div></div></div></div><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">It comes at the same time as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/space/nasa-starliner-boeing-noise-astronauts-stranded-update-b2606011.html\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">two pilots currently find themselves deserted on a spaceflight outside Earth&nbsp;</a>in an eerie echo of the events of 1970.</font></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">The original mission marked the greatest crisis in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/nasa\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">NASA</a>â€™s history, just nine months after Neil Armstrong first walked on the Moon. The team were halfway towards replicating Armstrongâ€™s success, when a stir of an oxygen tank damaged wire insulation causing an explosion which destroyed the vesselâ€™s entire oxygen supply. Back on Earth, Mission Control fought to enact an emergency operation to bring the men home.</font></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">â€œMore than 50 years after the mission, the film put me right back in the captainâ€™s seat,â€ Apollo 13 captain Lovell said in a statement. â€œThose were the days! Seeing the historic footage and hearing the perspectives of family and friends on the ground truly stirred my emotions.</font></p>', '2024-09-04 00:40:33', NULL, 1, 'Apollo-13:-Eerie-documentary-shows-what-itâ€™s-like-to-be-stranded-in-space', '7a3efe82bd2afd72064edb38aae7e43a.jpg'),
(43, 'Putin has two secret sons with gymnast who live life of luxury isolated from world', 8, 10, '<p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Russian president&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/vladimir-putin\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">Vladimir Putin</a>&nbsp;has&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/russia-ukraine-war-lviv-attack-putin-missiles-bombs-latest-b2607356.html\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">two secret sons&nbsp;</a>who live an isolated life of luxury in a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/indian-soldiers-stuck-russia-ukraine-war-b2605583.html\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">heavily-guarded mansion</a>, according to a Russian investigative journalism website.</font></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">The Dossier Centre&nbsp;reported that Ivan, nine, and Vladimir Jr, five, spend most of the year at<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/reviews/the-zelensky-story-bbc-ukraine-putin-b2606728.html\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">&nbsp;their fatherâ€™s vast mansion</a>&nbsp;near Lake Valdai, northwest of Moscow.</font></p><div id=\"article-im-prompt\" style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: medium;\"></div><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Their mother is Alina Kabaeva, the former Olympic rhythmic gymnast whose relationship with Putin has been&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/vladimir-putin-russia-election-how-long-b2607558.html\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">an open secret in Russia</a>&nbsp;for more than a decade,&nbsp;<a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://dossier.center/succession/\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">the Dossier Centre claim</a>.</font></p><div class=\"sc-w27hnf-3 iOJCvF desktop-only teads\" style=\"margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: medium;\"><div class=\"sc-1y9ieyw-0 joBdHo\" style=\"position: relative; max-width: 100%; justify-content: center; margin: 0px auto; background-color: transparent; clear: both;\"><div class=\"sc-1pfx6hk-0 lgUbTS\" style=\"max-width: 100%;\"><div data-mpu=\"true\" data-is-video=\"false\" data-tile-name=\"thirdparty01\" data-ad-unit-path=\"/71347885/_partner_independent/in_news/in_world/video/thirdparty01\" data-size-key=\"THIRD_PARTY_ARTICLE_BODY_DESKTOP\" data-refresh-check=\"false\" data-refresh-ms=\"150000\"></div></div></div></div><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">The two boys are surrounded by governesses, nannies, teachers and officers from the Kremlin Federal Guard and enjoy playing with a huge lego set and an iPad, the report said.</font></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">â€œThey have to play mostly alone or with adults,â€ the report, compiled with&nbsp;the help of a member of staff at the Valdai residence, said. â€œThey only see their parents late at night.â€</font></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">There are two ponies, rabbits, and a St Bernard dog which is cared for by Kremlin guards but lives with the family. The two children are believed to annoy Putin with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/disney-0\" style=\"color: rgb(236, 26, 46);\">Disney</a>&nbsp;cartoon impressions.</font></p><div class=\"sc-toncsa-0 gdPcRA\" style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: medium;\"></div><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Ivan was born in spring 2015 at the Santâ€™Anna maternity clinic in the Swiss city of Lugano, while Vladimir Jr was born in spring 2019 in Moscow, the report said.</font></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Putin has never made any direct reference to the boys. However, this week, he told schoolchildren in Siberia that, â€œMembers of my family, the little ones, speak Chinese.â€ They are also believed to be learning English and German.</font></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">The Dossier Centre said it had found pictures of Ivan but does not publish them for ethical reasons.</font></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">In the compound, staff are barred from leaving the grounds, but have use of a gym and tennis court. The salary on offer was Â£6,500 a month. The Dossier Centre said that turnover was high.</font></p><div class=\"sc-w27hnf-3 iOJCvF teads\" style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: medium;\"><div class=\"sc-1y9ieyw-0 joBdHo\" style=\"position: relative; max-width: 100%; justify-content: center; margin: 0px auto; background-color: transparent; clear: both;\"><div class=\"sc-1pfx6hk-0 lgUbTS\" style=\"max-width: 100%;\"><div data-mpu=\"true\" data-is-video=\"false\" data-tile-name=\"thirdparty02\" data-ad-unit-path=\"/71347885/_partner_independent/in_news/in_world/video/thirdparty02\" data-size-key=\"THIRD_PARTY_ARTICLE_BODY\" data-refresh-check=\"false\" data-refresh-ms=\"150000\"></div></div></div></div><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">The Putin sons cannot be found in government databases, from infancy they have cover documents, which are mostly made for spies and people under state protection.</font></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">â€œTheir dates of birth are only known by their immediate family. They donâ€™t fly on regular flights, they have separate planes,â€ the report said.</font></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">â€œThey donâ€™t attend kindergartens or schools, they are [taught by] hired governesses. They live in residences guarded by the FSO, sail on yachts and ride armoured trains.â€</font></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">In February and March the boys relocate to a luxury residence close to the Krasnaya Polyana resort, where they have been learning to ski.</font></p><p style=\"font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.44em; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">They spend July and August on luxury yachts, usually in the Gulf of Finland, on the Black Sea coast and Russiaâ€™s northern lakes. The boys travel by armoured train or private jet.</font></p>', '2024-09-05 23:08:27', NULL, 1, 'Putin-has-two-secret-sons-with-gymnast-who-live-life-of-luxury-isolated-from-world', '59656aa3aed8c39df2363bf7da0032b4.jpg');
